Package it.unive.lisa.cfg

Class Parameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unive.lisa.cfg.Parameter
  • public class Parameter
extends java.lang.Object
    A reference to a CFG parameter identified by its name and its type, containing the information about the source file, line and column where a parameter appears. No information about the CFG where the parameter appears is contained.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Parameter

        public Parameter​(java.lang.String name)
        Builds an untyped parameter reference, identified by its name. The location where this parameter reference happens is unknown (i.e. no source file/line/column is available) as well as its type (i.e. it is {#link Untyped#INSTANCE}).
        Parameters:
        name - the name of this parameter

      • Parameter

        public Parameter​(java.lang.String name,
                 Type staticType)
        Builds a typed parameter reference, identified by its name and its type. The location where this parameter reference happens is unknown (i.e. no source file/line/column is available).
        Parameters:
        name - the name of this parameter
        staticType - the type of this parameter

      • Parameter

        public Parameter​(java.lang.String sourceFile,
                 int line,
                 int col,
                 java.lang.String name,
                 Type staticType)
        Builds the parameter reference, identified by its name and its type, happening at the given location in the program.
        Parameters:
        sourceFile - the source file where this parameter happens. If unknown, use null
        line - the line number where this parameter happens in the source file. If unknown, use -1
        col - the column where this parameter happens in the source file. If unknown, use -1
        name - the name of this parameter
        staticType - the type of this parameter. If unknown, use Untyped.INSTANCE
